snippet.textDisplay:
Never thought I’d head talk about PC gaming being dead against consoles. Up until now all I ever heard was “are consoles obsolete?”

But also, I know Microsoft said the footage was in-engine but aren’t we fooled every year with this? Games at retail never look how they did when shown at an event. I mean, could it be that these graphics could have only been achieved running in-engine for a limited amount of time?

And could everything we saw be the ONLY things they had the series x play? It could have been scripted... doesn’t it take more power to run a game that has to adapt to whatever the player wants to do?

And if the “game” they showed really had no other levels or characters or anything else built, what if even with those limitations, the Series X could only run smoothly for those 2 minutes. Anything longer may over heat the system.

I dunno. Maybe I’m a pessimist but I like to trust history and we’ve always been given a lesser looking product than what is showcased.
